{"word":"H6166 - עֲרָד - ʻĂrâd - ar-awd' - Arad","slug":"H6166","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">עֲרָד</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʻĂrâd"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ar-awd'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Arad"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E2;&#x05E8;&#x05D3; - &#x201B;a&#x0306;ra&#x0302;d</b> - <i>ar-awd'</i><p/>From an unused root meaning to <i>sequester</i> itself; <i>fugitive</i>; <i>Arad</i>, the name of a place near Palestine, also of a Canaanite and an Israelite: - Arad."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H6165\">H6165</a>, <a href=\"#/H6170\">H6170</a>"}]}